    "## 4. Separating Logic from Execution\n",
    "\n",
    "### The `if __name__ == '__main__'` Pattern\n",
    "\n",
    "This Python idiom separates:\n",
    "- **Library code** (functions, classes) - can be imported\n",
    "- **Executable code** (scripts, main logic) - runs when file is executed\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why This Matters:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Reusability**: Import functions without running the script\n",
    "2. **Testing**: Test functions independently of execution logic\n",
    "3. **Organization**: Clear separation between 'what it does' and 'how it runs'\n",
    "4. **Collaboration**: Others can import your utilities safely\n",
    "\n",
    "### Structure:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "# All imports, constants, functions defined here...\n",
    "\n",
    "def main():\n",
    "    \"\"\"Main execution logic.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # This only runs when the file is executed directly\n",
    "    pass\n",
    "\n",
    "if __name__ == '__main__':\n",
    "    main()\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrating the __name__ == '__main__' Pattern\n",
    "print(\"=== SEPARATING LOGIC FROM EXECUTION ===\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "WITHOUT if __name__ == '__main__':\n",
    "========================================\n",
    "\n",
    "# health_utils.py\n",
    "def calculate_bmi(weight, height):\n",
    "    return weight / (height ** 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# This runs when the file is imported!\n",
    "result = calculate_bmi(70, 1.75)\n",
    "print(f\"BMI: {result}\")  # Executes on import!\n",
    "\n",
    "# main.py\n",
    "from health_utils import calculate_bmi\n",
    "# ^^^ This prints 'BMI: 22.86' just from importing!\n",
",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Problem: Code runs when imported, not just when executed!\")\n",
    "print(\"This makes the module unusable as a library.\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "WITH if __name__ == '__main__':\n",
    "========================================\n",
    "\n",
    "# health_utils.py\n",
    "def calculate_bmi(weight, height):\n",
    "    return weight / (height ** 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "def main():\n",
    "    # Demo code - only runs when file is executed directly\n",
    "    result = calculate_bmi(70, 1.75)\n",
    "    print(f\"BMI: {result}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if __name__ == '__main__':\n",
    "    main()\n",
    "\n",
    "# main.py\n",
    "from health_utils import calculate_bmi\n",
    "# ^^^ No output on import - clean!\n",
    "\n",
    "# Now use the function:\n",
    "patient_bmi = calculate_bmi(65, 1.70)\n",
    "print(f\"Patient BMI: {patient_bmi}\")\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Benefits:\")\n",
    "print(\"  • Can import without side effects\")\n",
    "print(\"  • Can run as standalone script\")\n",
    "print(\"  • Clear separation of library vs executable code\")\n",
    "print(\"  • Easier to test and reuse\")"
